			<div class="content" id="post-content-2554706">
									

<p>First-off, excellent job piling all this together. Thousands of responses is a LOT to go through, and the final product looks great.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Slight increases in the 'Male' and 'PNTS' categories while slight decreases in 'Female' and 'Other' categories are seen. Not a huge variation to draw conclusions from.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I kinda feel a little iffy about this. The 1.39% drop in the other/nb category is, for a percentage that was so minuscule to begin with, kind of significant. Same with women, except lesser so, given that the percentage was higher on average. I don't have a Point to make about it (this is more of a 'huh, that's weird' observation) but I feel like it's a weird decrease, and a thing to keep an eye on in coming months/years.</p>

							</div>

								
					
