					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205500" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1470886882 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Aug 2016 03:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2555482">
									

<p>Nice, Lurk. Awesome job putting this together :)</p>
<p>It's interesting to see a few things that I've wanted for years crop up in here, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Streamlined path to membership and posting, fewer restrictions</li>
<li>More leniency/encouragement of NSFW content</li>
<li>More encouragement of pictures, videos, audio logs, interactivity</li>
<li>&quot;Ease of use&quot; changes to the site layout (and I'm all for a new look)</li>
</ul>
<p>Those first two in particular have met with quite strong resistance in the past from veteran/staff users. I'm interested to know to what degree that's changed recently.</p>
<p>Also: Obviously, I'm picking out some stuff I agree with! I don't agree with decreasing actual standards for SCPs, for example, which is always a fairly popular cause. But still.</p>

							</div>

								
